To compute total income, the following conditions must be satisfied under Section 8 of the Income-Tax Act, 2025:
(a) The employee has received gratuity; 
(b) The employee is normally entitled to receive gratuity.

To recover tax arrears from a non-resident assessee, the following conditions must be satisfied under Section 421 of the Income-Tax Act, 2025:
(a) The tax due is not payable to the Government;
(b) The Government has no right to institute a suit for the recovery of the tax due from the assessee.

To invoke Section 13, a taxpayer must show that their total income falls under one of the specified heads of income, which includes:
(a) Salaries;
(b) Income from house property;
(c) Profits and gains of business or profession;
(d) Capital gains; and
(e) Income from other sources.

In order to invoke Section 13, a taxpayer must demonstrate that they have earned income from any of these categories.

