(a) The tax chargeable to the non-resident can be recovered by deduction under the provisions of Chapter XIX-B; 
(b) Any arrears of tax can also be recovered as per the provisions of this Act from any assets of the non-resident that are, or may at any time come, within India.

To claim a deduction under Section 10 of the Income Tax Act, 2025 (as amended by the Finance Act, 2026), the following eligibility conditions must be met:
(i) The patent should have been revoked by the Controller or the High Court under section 152;
(ii) The name of the assessee should have been excluded from the patents register as patentee; 
(iii) The deduction from the income attributable to the period during which the patent was revoked or the period for which the name of the assessee was excluded as patentee should be deemed to have been wrongly allowed.
